 1. Code of Conduct & Ethics Policy   
Policy Statement   
Barclays is commi Ʃed to maintaining the highest standards of integrity, accountability, and respect. 
The Barclays Way serves as the founda Ɵon for ethical behavior across all opera Ɵons, ensuring 
compliance with laws, regula Ɵons, and internal standards.   
Scope  
Applies to all employees, contractors, and thirdparty partners globally.  
Procedures   
 Ethical Standards: Employees must act honestly, avoid conﬂicts of interest, and report 
misconduct.  
 AnƟDiscrimina Ɵon: Strict prohibi Ɵon of discrimina Ɵon based on race, gender, age, disability, 
religion, or sexual orienta Ɵon.  
 Human Rights: Compliance with the Modern Slavery Act and Barclays’ Human Rights 
Statement.  
 Whistleblowing: Conﬁden Ɵal channels available for repor Ɵng unethical behavior without 
retaliaƟon.  
Responsibili Ɵes  
 Employees: Adhere to the Barclays Way and complete mandatory ethics training.  
 Managers: Reinforce ethical culture and address viola Ɵons promptly.   
 HR & Compliance: Monitor adherence and report to the Audit Commi Ʃee.  
Compliance Notes   
Annual review by Internal Audit; breaches may result in disciplinary ac Ɵon up to termina Ɵon.  
  
  
  
  
  
  
 
 
 
 
 2. Recruitment & Employment Policy   
Policy Statement   
Barclays ensures fair, transparent, and meritbased recruitment aligned with diversity and inclusion 
goals.  
Scope  
Covers all hiring processes globally, including permanent, temporary, and contract roles.  
Procedures   
 Job PosƟng: All vacancies adver Ɵsed internally and externally.   
 SelecƟon: Structured interviews,  competencybased assessments, 
and diversityinclusive panels.  
 Background Checks: Mandatory screening for ﬁnancial crime, regulatory compliance, and 
reputaƟonal risk.  
 ProbaƟon: Standard 6month proba Ɵon with structured performance reviews.   
Responsibili Ɵes  
 Recruiters: Ensure unbiased shortlis Ɵng.  
 Managers: Conduct fair interviews and onboarding.  
 HR: Maintain recruitment records and compliance with local labor laws.  
Compliance Notes   
Aligned with FCA/PRA regulatory expectaƟons; subject to annual HR audit.  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
 
 
 
 
  
  3. Compensa Ɵon & Beneﬁts Policy   
Policy Statement   
Barclays provides compe ƟƟve compensa Ɵon and beneﬁts to a Ʃract, retain, and mo Ɵvate employees 
while aligning with shareholder interests.  
Scope  
Applies to all employees globally, with localiza Ɵon for regional regula Ɵons.  
Procedures   
 Salary Reviews: Annual benchmarking against industry standards.  
 Variable Pay: Performancelinked bonuses Ɵed to risk management and compliance.   
 Beneﬁts: Health insurance, wellness programs, re Ɵrement savings, and parental leave.   
 Equity Programs: Longterm incen Ɵve plans for senior execu Ɵves.  
Responsibili Ɵes  
 HR Compensa Ɵon Team: Design pay structures and  monitor fairness.  
 Managers: Communicate pay decisions transparently.  
 Audit Commi Ʃee: Review  remunera Ɵon disclosures annually.  
Compliance Notes   
Disclosures aligned with UK Corporate Governance Code and 2024 remunera Ɵon report.  
  
  
  
  
 
 
 
 
 
  
  
  
  
  4. Performance Management Policy   
Policy Statement   
Barclays fosters a culture of accountability and con Ɵnuous improvement through structured 
performance management.  
Scope  
Applies to all employees globally.  
Procedures   
 Goal Seƫng: Annual  objecƟves aligned with business strategy.  
 MidYear Reviews: Formal checkins to assess progress.  
 YearEnd Appraisals: Ra Ɵngs based on performance, compliance, and risk behavior.   
 Career Development: Access to training, mentoring, and leadership programs.  
Responsibili Ɵes  
 Employees: Ac Ɵvely engage in feedback and development.   
 Managers: Provide construc Ɵve feedback and coaching.   
 HR: Monitor consistency and fairness across evalua Ɵons.  
Compliance Notes   
Performance ra Ɵngs linked to  remunera Ɵon; subject to audit oversight.  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
 
 
 
 
  5. Workplace Culture & Employee Engagement Policy   
Policy Statement   
Barclays promotes a posi Ɵve, inclusive, and ﬂexible workplace culture that values employee voice.   
Scope  
Applies to all employees globally.  
Procedures   
 Flexible Work: Hybrid models, remote work op Ɵons, and ﬂexible hours.   
 Leave Policies: Annual, parental, sick, and sabba Ɵcal leave provisions.   
 Engagement Surveys: Annual surveys with ac Ɵon plans for improvement.   
 Employee Resource Groups: Support for diversity networks (e.g., gender, LGBTQ+, disability).  
