Policy 3: IT Opera Ɵons & Resilience Policy   
1. Purpose & Scope   
This policy deﬁnes Barclays’ approach to ensuring IT opera Ɵonal resilience, business con Ɵnuity, and 
disaster recovery. It applies to:   
 All Barclays IT systems, applica Ɵons, and infrastructure globally.   
 All employees, contractors, and third-party service providers.   
 All business units and subsidiaries, including joint ventures.   
The objecƟve is to ensure that Barclays can withstand, respond to, and recover from opera Ɵonal 
disrupƟons while  maintaining  criƟcal services for customers, regulators, and stakeholders.   
  
2. Governance & Accountability   
 Board Oversight:  The Risk Commi Ʃee and Audit Commi Ʃee oversee resilience planning.   
 Chief Opera Ɵng Oﬃcer (COO):  Accountable for IT opera Ɵons and resilience strategy.   
 Resilience Steering Commi Ʃee: Cross-func Ɵonal body responsible for resilience tes Ɵng and 
reporƟng.  
 Internal Audit:  Conducts annual reviews of resilience controls and recovery capabili Ɵes.  
  
3. Business Con Ɵnuity Management (BCM)   
 CriƟcal Services Iden ƟﬁcaƟon: Barclays idenƟﬁes criƟcal services (payments, trading, 
customer access) and  maps dependencies.   
 Recovery Objec Ɵves:   
o Recovery Time Objec Ɵve (RTO): ≤ 4 hours for cri Ɵcal services.   
o Recovery Point Objec Ɵve (RPO): ≤ 15 minutes for cri Ɵcal data.  
 ConƟnuity Plans:  Each business unit  maintains  documented con Ɵnuity plans.   
 TesƟng: Annual con Ɵnuity exercises across all regions.   
  
 
 
 
 
 
 
4. Disaster Recovery (DR)   
 Data Centres: Barclays operates redundant data  centres with geographic separa Ɵon.  
 Cloud Resilience:  Hybrid cloud adop Ɵon with mul Ɵ-region failover.   
 Backup Strategy:    
o Daily backups for cri Ɵcal systems.   
o Weekly full backups  retained for 12 months.   
o Oﬀsite storage for disaster scenarios.   
 DR Drills:  Semi-annual disaster recovery drills simula Ɵng cybera Ʃacks, natural disasters, and 
system failures.   
  
5. Change Management   
 Approval Process:  All IT changes require documented approval and rollback plans.   
 SegregaƟon of DuƟes: Developers cannot deploy directly to produc Ɵon.  
 Audit Trails:  All changes logged and  retained for 7 years.   
 Emergency Changes:  Allowed only with CISO/COO approval, documented post-
implementa Ɵon.  
  
6. Cloud Security & Resilience   
 Cloud Adop Ɵon: Barclays uses hybrid cloud with strict iden Ɵty and access management.   
 Resilience Standards:  Cloud providers must meet Barclays’ encryp Ɵon and failover 
requirements.   
 Monitoring:  ConƟnuous monitoring of cloud workloads.   
 Exit Strategy:  Documented plans for cloud provider exit or migra Ɵon.  
  
7. Resilience Tes Ɵng  
 Scenario Tes Ɵng: Barclays conducts resilience tests for cybera Ʃacks, pandemics, and 
geopoliƟcal disrup Ɵons.  
 Tabletop Exercises:  Quarterly exercises with senior management.   
 Live Simula Ɵons: Annual live simula Ɵons involving IT, opera Ɵons, and business units.   
 Metrics: Test results documented and reported to the Board.   
  
 
8. OperaƟonal KPIs   
 System Up Ɵme: ≥ 99.95% for cri Ɵcal systems.   
 Incident Response Time:  ≤ 1 hour for cri Ɵcal incidents.   
 Patch Compliance Rate:  ≥ 95% within required Ɵmelines.  
 Resilience Test Pass Rate:  ≥ 90% across all scenarios.   
  
9. Third-Party & Outsourcing Risk   
 Vendor Resilience Standards:  Vendors must  demonstrate  resilience capabili Ɵes.  
 Contractual Obliga Ɵons: SLAs must include resilience metrics.   
 Monitoring:  ConƟnuous vendor risk assessments.   
 Exit Planning:  Documented con Ɵngency plans for vendor failure.   
  
10. Compliance & Regula Ɵon  
 FCA/PRA Opera Ɵonal Resilience Framework:  Full compliance with UK regulatory 
