11. Metrics & KPIs   
 Data Breach Response Time:  ≤ 72 hours for regulatory no ƟﬁcaƟon.  
 Training Comple Ɵon Rate: ≥ 95% of employees annually.   
 Vendor Compliance Rate:  ≥ 90% of vendors  meeƟng Barclays’ privacy standards.   
 Data Subject Request Fulﬁllment:  ≥ 95% requests fulﬁlled within statutory Ɵmelines.  
  
12. Enforcement   
 ViolaƟons: May result in disciplinary ac Ɵon, up to termina Ɵon.  
 Audit: Internal Audit reviews compliance annually.   
 ConƟnuous Improvement:  Policy updated annually to reﬂect new regula Ɵons and threats.   
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
Policy 5: Employee & Insider Risk Policy   
1. Purpose & Scope   
This policy  establishes  Barclays’ approach to managing insider risk, ensuring employees and 
contractors act responsibly, and protec Ɵng the organiza Ɵon against internal threats. It applies to:   
 All Barclays employees, contractors, and third-party vendors with system or data access.   
 All business units and subsidiaries globally.   
 All systems, applica Ɵons, and processes where insider ac Ɵvity could  impact conﬁdenƟality, 
integrity, or availability.   
The objecƟve is to miƟgate risks arising from human error, negligence, or malicious insider ac Ɵvity 
while fostering a culture of accountability and trust.   
  
2. Governance & Accountability   
 Board Oversight:  The Risk Commi Ʃee and Audit Commi Ʃee oversee insider risk 
management.   
 Chief Human Resources Oﬃcer (CHRO):  Accountable for employee conduct and insider risk 
programs.   
 Chief Informa Ɵon Security Oﬃcer (CISO):  Accountable for monitoring insider ac Ɵvity and 
reporƟng to the Group Risk Commi Ʃee.  
 Insider Risk Management Team:  Cross-func Ɵonal body including HR, Legal, Compliance, and 
IT Security.   
 Internal Audit:  Conducts annual reviews of insider risk controls.   
  
3. Employee Onboarding & Screening   
 Background Checks:  Mandatory for all new hires, including criminal, ﬁnancial, and reference 
checks.  
 Access Provisioning:  Access granted only a Ōer comple Ɵon of onboarding and training.   
 ConﬁdenƟality Agreements:  All employees must sign conﬁden Ɵality agreements before 
system access.   
 Role-Based Access:  Access aligned with job responsibili Ɵes, reviewed quarterly.   
  
 
 
 
 
4. Acceptable Use Policy   
 System Usage:  Employees must use Barclays systems only for authorized business purposes.   
 Personal Devices (BYOD):  Allowed only under Mobile Device Management (MDM) controls.   
 Email & Internet Use:  Restricted to professional ac ƟviƟes; monitoring in place.   
 Prohibited Ac ƟviƟes: Unauthorized downloads, use of unapproved cloud services, and data 
exﬁltraƟon.  
  
5. Monitoring & Detec Ɵon  
 User AcƟvity Monitoring:  High-risk ac ƟviƟes ﬂagged for review (e.g., mass downloads, 
unusual access Ɵmes).  
 Behavioral Analy Ɵcs: AI-driven monitoring of anomalous employee behavior.   
 Privileged User Monitoring:  Enhanced monitoring for administrators and developers.   
 Audit Logging:  Immutable logs  retained for 7 years.   
  
6. Training & Awareness   
 Mandatory Training:  Annual insider risk and cybersecurity awareness training.   
 Phishing Simula Ɵons: Quarterly exercises to test employee resilience.   
 Role-Speciﬁc Training:  Enhanced training for privileged users and developers.   
 Culture of Responsibility:  Employees encouraged to report suspicious ac Ɵvity without fear 
of reprisal.   
  
7. Incident Response & Escala Ɵon  
 Insider Threat Response Plan:  Deﬁnes roles, responsibili Ɵes, and escala Ɵon paths.   
 EscalaƟon Protocols:    
o Level 1: Local HR/IT team.   
o Level 2: Insider Risk Management Team.   
o Level 3: Group CISO and Board  noƟﬁcaƟon.  
 Post-Incident Review:  Root cause analysis and lessons learned documented within 7 days.   
 Disciplinary Ac Ɵon: May include suspension, termina Ɵon, or legal proceedings.   
  
 
 
8. Whistleblowing & Repor Ɵng  
 Whistleblowing Hotline:  Anonymous repor Ɵng channel available globally.   
 ProtecƟon: Whistleblowers protected against retalia Ɵon.  
 InvesƟgaƟon: All reports inves Ɵgated promptly by HR and Compliance.   
 Transparency:  Outcomes reported to the Audit Commi Ʃee.  
  
9. Third-Party & Contractor Risk   
 Vendor Screening:  Contractors subject to background checks and access restric Ɵons.  
 Access Controls:  Contractors granted Ɵme-bound, role-based access.   
 Monitoring:  Contractor ac Ɵvity monitored  conƟnuously.  
 Exit Procedures:  Contractor access revoked  immediately  upon contract termina Ɵon.  
  
10. Compliance & Regula Ɵon  
 GDPR & UK Data Protec Ɵon Act: Insider monitoring aligned with privacy obliga Ɵons.  
