Policy 6: Emerging Technology & AI Policy   
1. Purpose & Scope   
This policy  establishes  Barclays’ approach to adop Ɵng, governing, and securing emerging 
technologies, with a par Ɵcular focus on Ar Ɵﬁcial Intelligence (AI). It applies to:   
 All Barclays employees, contractors, and third-party vendors  involved in technology 
development, deployment, or oversight.   
 All AI systems, machine learning models, and emerging technologies (cloud, blockchain, 
quantum compu Ɵng, etc.) used within Barclays.   
 All business units and subsidiaries globally.   
The objecƟve is to ensure that emerging technologies are deployed responsibly, ethically, securely, 
and in compliance with regulatory requirements.   
  
2. Governance & Accountability   
 Board Oversight:  The Technology Commi Ʃee and Risk Commi Ʃee oversee emerging 
technology adop Ɵon.  
 Chief Technology Oﬃcer (CTO):  Accountable for emerging technology strategy.   
 Chief Informa Ɵon Security Oﬃcer (CISO):  Accountable for security risks associated with  new 
technologies.   
 AI Governance Council:  Cross-func Ɵonal body including Risk, Compliance, Legal, and 
Technology teams.   
 Internal Audit:  Conducts annual reviews of AI and emerging technology governance.   
  
3. AI Governance Framework   
 Ethical Principles:  AI systems must be fair, transparent, accountable, and aligned with 
Barclays’ Code of Conduct.   
 Bias Monitoring:  AI models tested regularly for bias and discriminatory outcomes.   
 Explainability:  AI decisions must be  explainable  to regulators, customers, and internal 
stakeholders.   
 Human Oversight:  CriƟcal AI decisions (e.g., credit scoring, fraud detec Ɵon) require human 
validaƟon.  
 Lifecycle Management:  AI models documented, version-controlled, and subject to periodic 
review.  
  
 
 
4. Security & Risk Management   
 AI-Speciﬁc Threats:  Monitoring for  adversarial a Ʃacks, model poisoning, and deepfake 
fraud.  
 Data Security:  Training data must be anonymized, encrypted, and sourced responsibly.   
 Access Controls:  Role-based access to AI models and datasets.   
 Incident Response:  AI-related incidents escalated through Barclays’ SOC and IRP.   
 Third-Party Risk:  Vendors providing AI solu Ɵons must comply with  Barclays’ security 
standards.   
  
5. Emerging Technology Adop Ɵon  
 Cloud Compu Ɵng: Hybrid cloud adop Ɵon with strict iden Ɵty and access management.   
 Blockchain:  Used only for approved ﬁnancial services with regulatory compliance.   
 Quantum Compu Ɵng: Research monitored for  potenƟal cryptographic risks.   
 AutomaƟon & Robo Ɵcs: Deployed with safeguards to prevent opera Ɵonal disrup Ɵon.  
 InnovaƟon Labs: Emerging technologies tested in controlled environments before 
producƟon deployment.   
  
6. Regulatory Compliance   
 GDPR & UK Data Protec Ɵon Act: AI systems must  comply with  data protec Ɵon 
requirements.   
 FCA/PRA Requirements:  Emerging technologies integrated into opera Ɵonal resilience 
frameworks.   
 EU AI Act:  Compliance with European AI regula Ɵons.  
 ISO/IEC 23894:  Alignment with interna Ɵonal AI risk management standards.   
  
7. Employee Awareness & Training   
 Mandatory Training:  Annual training on AI ethics and emerging technology risks.   
 Specialist Training:  Advanced training for developers, data scien Ɵsts, and risk managers.   
 Awareness Campaigns:  Regular updates on emerging threats (e.g., deepfakes, quantum 
risks).  
 ReporƟng Culture:  Employees encouraged to report concerns about AI or emerging 
technology misuse.   
  
8. Metrics & KPIs   
 AI Model Review Rate:  ≥ 95% of models reviewed annually.   
 Bias Detec Ɵon Rate: ≥ 90% of models tested for bias.   
 Vendor Compliance Rate:  ≥ 90% of vendors  meeƟng Barclays’ AI standards.   
 Training Comple Ɵon Rate: ≥ 95% of employees annually.   
  
9. ConƟnuous Improvement   
 Annual Review:  Policy updated annually to reﬂect  new technologies  and regulatory 
