Policy 7: Audit & Con Ɵnuous Improvement Policy   
1. Purpose & Scope   
This policy  establishes  Barclays’ approach to audi Ɵng IT and cybersecurity controls, monitoring 
compliance, and driving con Ɵnuous improvement across technology and risk management func Ɵons. 
It applies to:   
 All Barclays IT systems, applica Ɵons, and infrastructure globally.   
 All employees, contractors, and third-party vendors.   
 All business units and subsidiaries, including joint ventures.   
The objecƟve is to ensure that IT and cybersecurity prac Ɵces remain eﬀecƟve, resilient, and aligned 
with regulatory requirements and industry best prac Ɵces.  
  
2. Governance & Accountability   
 Board Oversight:  The Audit Commi Ʃee and Risk Commi Ʃee oversee IT audit and con Ɵnuous 
improvement ac ƟviƟes.  
 Chief Audit Execu Ɵve (CAE): Accountable for internal audit strategy and repor Ɵng.  
 Chief Informa Ɵon Security Oﬃcer (CISO):  Accountable for cybersecurity audit readiness and 
remediaƟon.  
 ConƟnuous Improvement Council:  Cross-func Ɵonal body including Audit, Risk, Compliance, 
and Technology teams.   
 External Assurance:  Independent external auditors engaged annually to  validate IT and cyber 
resilience.   
  
3. Audit Framework   
 Internal Audit:  Annual audits of IT opera Ɵons, cybersecurity, and data privacy controls.   
 Risk-Based Approach:  Audit priori Ɵes determined  by risk assessments and regulatory 
requirements.   
 Control Tes Ɵng: Key controls tested for design and opera Ɵng eﬀecƟveness.  
 Audit Trails:  All IT changes, incidents, and access logs  retained for 7 years.   
 ReporƟng: Audit ﬁndings reported to the Audit Commi Ʃee and Board.   
  
 
 
 
 
4. ConƟnuous Monitoring   
 Key Risk Indicators (KRIs):  Deﬁned for cyber incidents, system down Ɵme, and vendor 
compliance.   
 Key Performance Indicators (KPIs):    
o Incident response Ɵme.  
o Patch compliance  rate.  
o Training comple Ɵon rate.  
o Vendor compliance  rate.  
 Dashboards:  Real-Ɵme dashboards provided to senior management.   
 Automated Alerts:  SOC generates alerts for devia Ɵons from resilience thresholds.   
  
5. ConƟnuous Improvement Cycle   
 Plan: IdenƟfy risks, set objecƟves, and deﬁne improvement ini ƟaƟves.  
 Do: Implement controls, training, and technology enhancements.   
 Check: Audit and  monitor performance against KPIs.   
 Act: Remediate gaps, update policies, and enhance resilience.   
 Annual Review:  Policies updated annually to reﬂect new threats and regulatory changes.   
  
6. Incident & Breach Reviews   
 Post-Incident Analysis:  Root cause analysis conducted within 7 days of major incidents.   
 Lessons Learned:  Incorporated into updated controls and training programs.   
 Board Repor Ɵng: Signiﬁcant incidents reported to the Board with remedia Ɵon plans.  
 Regulatory Engagement:  Regulators informed of material incidents and correc Ɵve acƟons.  
  
7. Vendor & Third-Party Assurance   
 Vendor Audits:  Annual audits of cri Ɵcal vendors’ IT and cybersecurity prac Ɵces.  
 Contractual Obliga Ɵons: Vendors required to provide audit rights and compliance evidence.   
 ConƟnuous Monitoring:  Vendor compliance tracked via dashboards.   
 Exit Strategy:  ConƟngency plans for vendor failure or non-compliance.   
  
 
8. Regulatory Compliance   
 FCA/PRA Requirements:  Audit and improvement aligned with UK opera Ɵonal resilience 
frameworks.   
 GDPR & UK Data Protec Ɵon Act: Privacy audits conducted annually.   
 NIS2 Direc Ɵve (EU): Applies to European opera Ɵons.  
 ISO 27001 & ISO 27701:  Alignment with interna Ɵonal informa Ɵon security and privacy 
standards.   
  
9. Employee Engagement   
 Training: Annual audit awareness training for employees.   
 Feedback Mechanisms:  Employees encouraged to suggest improvements.   
 Whistleblowing:  Anonymous repor Ɵng channels for audit or compliance concerns.   
 RecogniƟon: Employees recognized for contribu Ɵons to con Ɵnuous improvement.   
  
10. Metrics & KPIs   
 Audit Comple Ɵon Rate: ≥ 95% of planned audits annually.   
 RemediaƟon Closure Rate:  ≥ 90% of audit ﬁndings closed within agreed Ɵmelines.  
 ConƟnuous Improvement Ini ƟaƟves: ≥ 80% completed annually.   
