INSERT INTO public.chunks VALUES ('c54b6237-dd75-449f-a879-b8ce59ca876c', '0118000e-36b8-4aa9-a8b5-77609146d5e4', 'The Raising Concerns process  
Overview s 
Barclays is commi Ʃed to providing a  respecƞul and inclusive environment to work in and colleagues 
are encouraged to speak up about ac Ɵons and behaviours that have no place in the organisaƟon.  We 
encourage colleagues to raise concerns directly to their management, Compliance, HR or Legal.  
However, some Ɵmes colleagues do not feel comfortable using these avenues.  To help them, Barclays 
has a dedicated and impar Ɵal Raising Concerns process, through which colleagues can report their 
concerns in the know ledge that the reports will be taken seriously and managed sensi Ɵvely and 
conﬁdenƟally.   
When to use the Raising Concerns process  
Barclays takes all concerns raised seriously and you are encouraged to raise any concern you have 
through usual channels.  
If you are a customer or client and have a ques Ɵon or complaint  regarding our products or services, 
please submit it one of these ways  or by contac Ɵng your exis Ɵng relaƟonship team, should you 
have one.  If you are an employee or contractor you are encouraged to raise your concern directly 
with your line management or a contact in the HR, Compliance or Legal func Ɵons.  
If either (a). you do not fall into one of the groups above; or (b). you do and you are not comfortable 
contacƟng us via the usual channels and you believe that your concern amounts to a  whistleblow, 
then we encourage you to contact the Raising Concerns team using the contact details below.  We 
explain what we mean by whistleblowing below.  
A concern rela Ɵng purely to the product or service provided to you is unlikely to be classiﬁed as 
a whistleblow. This is because whistleblowing relates to concerns which fall within the wider public 
interest. For example, concerns about breaches of our policies and procedures and breaches of laws 
and regula Ɵon may be assessed as  whistleblows by the Raising Concerns team. Reports 
of behaviour that may be harmful to Barclays and the communi Ɵes we serve could also be assessed 
as whistleblows.  
What happens to concerns raised through the Raising Concerns process  
The Raising Concerns team will assess the concerns raised and refer them to the most appropriate 
team for review and, where appropriate, inves ƟgaƟon.   This includes concerns assessed by the team 
as whistleblowing; they will be referred to the specialist and impar Ɵal whistleblowing team in group 
Barclays Compliance to inves Ɵgate further.  In such  cases, the whistleblowing team will contact you 
to explain the inves ƟgaƟon process to you.    
All concerns raised to the Raising Concerns team are taken seriously. No one should experience any 
